            <h2><a name="Ways_to_Communicate"></a>Ways to Communicate</h2>
            <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr>
                <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="10"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><ul>
                          <li> You can talk to other penguins by chatting, using emotes, and doing actions.</li>
                          <li> To chat, if your account settings are set to Standard Safe Chat, you can either type in the text box at the bottom of the screen and press enter or click &lsquo;send&rsquo;; or, you can use the menu on the left.</li>
                          <li>If your penguin does not have a text box to type in messages, you are set to Ultimate Safe Chat. </li>
                          <li>In Ultimate Safe Chat, you cannot type in messages, but can communicate using the Ultimate Safe Chat menu on the left, as well as by emotes, actions, and greeting cards. </li>
                          <li><strong>Note:</strong> If you are in Ultimate Safe Chat mode, you will only see other Ultimate Safe Chat messages, as well as actions, emotes, and greeting cards.</li>
                          <li>You can easily <a href="safety.htm#Changing_Safe_Chat_Level">Change Your Safe Chat Level.</a> </li>
                      </ul></td>
                    </tr>
                </table></td>
                <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/ways-communicate.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </div>
            <h2><a name="Send_Post_Card" id="Send_Post_Card"></a>How to Send a Post Card </h2>
            <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr>
                <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="10"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><ul>
                          <li>To send a post card to another penguin, you first need to open their player card. </li>
                          <ul>
                            <li>If they&rsquo;re in the same room as you, click on their penguin. </li>
                            <li>Or, you can click on your buddies list (Smiley Face icon, third from the right on your bottom menu), and click on their name. </li>
                          </ul>
                          <li>Once you have their player card open, click the envelope icon on their card to &ldquo;send mail&rdquo;. </li>
                          <li>This will open the Post Card Catalog. </li>
                          <li>Pick the card you want to send (they cost 10 coins), and click &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; to send the card. </li>
                      </ul></td>
                    </tr>
                </table></td>
                <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/post-card.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </div>
            <h2><a name="Breaking_the_Rules"></a>Breaking the Rules</h2>
            <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr>
                <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="10"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td height="80"><ul>
                          <li> If you swear or say something against the rules, you will be banned. This means you will not be able to use your account for a period of time &ndash; anywhere from 24 hours to forever. </li>
                          <li> If you are a member and you are banned, you will <strong>not</strong> be reimbursed for the time that you were banned. </li>
                          <li> A ban can happen automatically, which takes effect instantly, or be assigned by a moderator, which may take a little more time. </li>
                          <li>Learn more on<a href="../faq/policy-cheating.htm"> Club Penguin rules</a>. </li>
                      </ul></td>
                    </tr>
                </table></td>
                <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/breaking-rules.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </div>
            <h2><a name="Banned_Penguin"></a>How a Penguin is Banned </h2>
            <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr>
                <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="10"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td height="80"><p>A penguin can be banned either automatically or by a moderator. </p>
                          <ul>
                            <li> An Automatic Ban occurs instantly when the player has said one of several flagged bad words. </li>
                            <li> A Moderator Ban happens when: </li>
                            <ul>
                              <li> A player reports another player; </li>
                              <li>A record of all conversation at that time in that room is sent to the moderators, including filtered messages;</li>
                              <li>A moderator reviews the conversation;</li>
                              <li><strong>If</strong> the moderator sees bad language or inappropriate behavior, they will ban the guilty penguin 24 hours for a first-time offense or 72 hours for a second or third offense. </li>
                              <li> Four or more offenses may result in a permanent ban.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </ul></td>
                    </tr>
                </table></td>
                <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/banned-login.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </div>
           <br>
<h2><a name="Emotes"></a>Emotes</h2>
              <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                <tr>
                  <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td height="10"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><ul>
                            <li>
                              <p>You can communicate by using the emotes and actions. Emotes, or emoticons, are small icons displaying a thought or emotion. Your emotes button is on the left of the toolbar. You can also display emotes by using <a href="navigation.htm#Quick_Keys">Quick Keys</a>. </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                  <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                  <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/emotes.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
                </tr>
              </table>
              <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </div>
		  <br>

              
              <h2><a name="Actions"></a>Actions</h2>
              <table width="718" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                <tr>
                  <td width="358" valign="top"><table width="358" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td height="10"></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><ul>
                            <li>Your penguin can do certain actions &ndash; wave, dance, sit, and throw a snowball. To do one of the actions, click on the actions icon &ndash; the sitting penguin (on the left side of your bottom menu). Then click on the action you want to do (sit, wave, or dance). </li>
                            <li> If you want to sit down, click the direction you want to face in the action menu. </li>
                            <li> You can also use <a href="navigation.htm#Quick_Keys">Quick Keys</a> to do actions. </li>
                          </ul>
                            <p><strong>Snowballs:</strong></p>
                            <ul>
                              <li> Another action you can do is throw a snowball. </li>
                              <li> To throw a snowball, click the Snowball icon (on the left of the toolbar), and then click a target. </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                  <td width="10" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                  <td width="350" valign="top"><img src="../../images/screenshots/actions.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
                </tr>
              </table>
              <div align="right">
                <p><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>
